    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/163</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-01T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1709. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1. Legation’s 2929, March 24. Board approves the new agreement on exportation
                    of cotton. It should be stated, however, that we have no embargo on cotton into
                    Switzerland but must adhere to the ration figure of our agreement. Concerning
                    possibility of affording market here for cotton goods, etc., our reply will
                    follow later.</p>
                <p>Beginning now Board will number serially all cables for you and it is suggested
                    you do likewise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
